<!--
  --- Question 2 ---
  This component represents the second question in the quiz.
-->

<div class="question-card" id="card-1" data-qid="1" data-type="multi" data-choose="2">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 02</span>
    <span class="q-case-tag">Case A</span>
    <span class="q-tag multi">Choose 2</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      Which <strong>two</strong> functions are performed at the <strong>MAC sublayer</strong> of the OSI Data Link Layer
      to facilitate Ethernet communication?
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-1">
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">applies delimiting of Ethernet frame fields to synchronize communication between nodes</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">applies source and destination MAC addresses to Ethernet frame</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">places information in the Ethernet frame that identifies which network layer protocol is being encapsulated by the frame</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">handles communication between upper layer networking software and Ethernet NIC hardware</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="4">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">E</span>
        <span class="opt-text">adds Ethernet control information to network protocol data</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn multi-pending" id="submit-1" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
      <span class="pending-count" id="pendingCount-1">0 / 2 selected</span>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-1">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-1"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        The <strong>MAC (Media Access Control)</strong> sublayer handles two core responsibilities in Ethernet:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Frame delimiting</strong> &mdash; synchronizes nodes by marking frame boundaries</li>
          <li><strong>MAC addressing</strong> &mdash; applies source &amp; destination hardware addresses to frames</li>
        </ul>
        The other options (C, D, E) describe LLC sublayer duties or higher-layer networking roles.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pagination-controls">
      <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-1">Previous</button>
      <span class="page-indicator">2 / 2</span>
      <button class="nav-btn" id="next-1">Finish</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
